content: Yu Zhang | ASU Search Yu Zhang Associate Professor, School of Computing and Augmented Intelligence [email protected] Mail code: 8809 Campus: Tempe ‌ Long Bio Yu (Tony) Zhang, an assistant professor in computer science and engineering in the School for Computing and Augmented Intelligence at Arizona State University. He earned his master’s degree and doctorate in computer science from the University of Tennessee, Knoxville. Previously, Zhang worked as a postdoctoral research scholar and a research assistant professor at Arizona State University. Zhang’s research interests include distributed robot systems, human-robot interaction, multi-agent systems, human-aware planning, multi-agent planning and automated planning and scheduling.
